<h2 class="art-postheader">Coronavirus Update 3/13/2020</h2>
<div class="art-postcontent">
    <!-- article-content -->
<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">
<p>Parents,</p>
<p> I just want to brief you on the plans we are currently working on at Sleepy Eye Public school in the midst of this coronavirus outbreak.</p>
<p>1.We are going to follow all protocols in regards to proper hygiene and handwashing including the use of antiseptic hand soaps.</p>
<p>2.We discussed two potential school closing options in case the Coronavirus Pandemic affects our school district.</p>
<p style="margin-left:.5in;">A:  The Governor directs the Commissioner of Education to close all Minnesota schools. In this case if we are unable to meet the 165 days minimum attendance requirement, schools are able to submit an application to MDE to have the minimum requirements waived.</p>
<p style="margin-left:.5in;">B: If the Sleepy Eye School administrator’s chooses to close schools independently without the Governor’s directive, we would have to follow our snow day routine protocol. In this case if we would not meet the 165 days minimum requirements after using up our 5 digital days (we have 3 left unless the legislature changes the current statue) we would have to make up days to reach the 165 days of instruction.</p>
<p style="margin-left:.5in;">My plan is to use digital days in both scenarios but not every day. I was thinking of doing every other day or something similar to that and still try not to dip below the 165 day minimum if it is possible.</p>
<p>3.We discussed the potential cancelation/postponement of some of our school events that draws large public attendance such as the grandparent’s day, concerts…. I made the decision to cancel the senior trip to Florida. Mr. Laffen and the advisors will be working with the travel agent to sort the situation out and will inform the students as well. I also plan on postponing the grandparent day to “wait and see how things progress” and we’ll make a determination closer to the April 8<sup>th</sup> date.  </p>
<p>5.The elementary school will start sending devices home with students that have no access to hardware at home.</p>
<p>6.We will follow the directive of the Minnesota State High School League about our spring activities.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>We are taking the matter seriously and will act in the best interest of our students and staff to keep everyone safe.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>John Cselovszki<br>Superintendent/Elementary Principal<br>Sleepy Eye Public Schools</p>
